    <briefdescription>
<para>An <ref refid="classiceberg_1_1rest_1_1auth_1_1AuthSession" kindref="compound">AuthSession</ref> that signs requests with AWS SigV4. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>The request is first authenticated by the delegate <ref refid="classiceberg_1_1rest_1_1auth_1_1AuthSession" kindref="compound">AuthSession</ref> (e.g., OAuth2), then signed with SigV4. In case of conflicting headers, the Authorization header set by the delegate is relocated with an &quot;Original-&quot; prefix, then included in the canonical headers to sign.</para>
<para>See <ulink url="https://docs.aws.amazon.com/IAM/latest/UserGuide/reference_sigv.html">https://docs.aws.amazon.com/IAM/latest/UserGuide/reference_sigv.html</ulink></para>
<para>Thread safety: <ref refid="classiceberg_1_1rest_1_1auth_1_1SigV4AuthSession_1a04f0085438eddb1c623157a11073aa24" kindref="member">Authenticate()</ref> is thread-safe as long as the delegate session is. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
